\f0\i0\b0  have corresponding meanings.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 9  Meaning of 
\f3\i cyber security incident
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	A 
\f3\i\b cyber security incident
\f2\b0  
\f0\i0 is one or more acts, events or circumstances:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	of a kind covered by the meaning of 
\f3\i\b cyber security incident 
\f0\i0\b0 in the 
\f2\i Security of Critical Infrastructure Act 2018
\f0\i0 ; or\
	(b)	involving unauthorised impairment of electronic communication to or from a computer, within the meaning of that phrase in that Act, but as if that phrase did not exclude the mere interception of any such communication.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	However, an incident is only a 
\f3\i\b cyber security incident
\f0\i0\b0  for the purposes of this Act if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the incident involves a critical infrastructure asset; or\
	(b)	the incident involves the activities of an entity that is a corporation to which paragraph\'a051(xx) of the Constitution applies; or\
	(c)	the incident is or was effected by means of a telegraphic, telephonic or other like service within the meaning of paragraph\'a051(v) of the Constitution (including, for example, by means of the internet); or\
	(d)	the incident is impeding or impairing, or has impeded or impaired, the ability of a computer to connect to such a service; or\
	(e)	the incident has seriously prejudiced or is seriously prejudicing:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the social or economic stability of Australia or its people; or\
	(ii)	the defence of Australia; or\
	(iii)	national security.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 10  Meaning of 
\f3\i permitted cyber security purpose
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Each of the following is a 
\f3\i\b permitted cyber security purpose
\f2\b0  
\f0\i0 for a cyber security incident:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the performance of the functions of a Commonwealth body (to the extent that it is not a Commonwealth enforcement body) relating to responding to, mitigating or resolving the cyber security incident;\
	(b)	the performance of the functions of a State body relating to responding to, mitigating or resolving the cyber security incident;\
	(c)	the performance of the functions of the National Cyber Security Coordinator under Part\'a04
\f2\i  
\f0\i0 relating to the cyber security incident;\
	(d)	informing and advising the Minister, and other Ministers of the Commonwealth, about the cyber security incident;\
	(e)	preventing or mitigating material risks that the cyber security incident has seriously prejudiced, is seriously prejudicing, or could reasonably be expected to prejudice:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the social or economic stability of Australia or its people; or\
	(ii)	the defence of Australia; or\
	(iii)	national security;\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(f)	preventing or mitigating material risks to a critical infrastructure asset;\
	(g)	the performance of the functions of an intelligence agency;\
	(h)	the performance of the functions of a Commonwealth enforcement body.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note 1:	There are some limitations in relation to civil or regulatory functions against entities that have provided information in relation to the incident: see subsections\'a038(2) and 39(3).\
Note 2:	Certain information must not be disclosed to a State body under Parts of this Act unless a Minister of the State or Territory has consented to those Parts applying to the State body: see section\'a011.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 11  Disclosure to State body\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	Despite any other provision of this Act, information that may be disclosed to a State body under Part\'a03, 4 or 5 must not be disclosed to the State body under that Part unless:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a Minister of the State or Territory has informed the Minister administering this Act, in writing, that the State or Territory gives consent to the provisions of that Part applying to the State body; and\
	(b)	a Minister of the State or Territory has not informed the Minister administering this Act, in writing, that the State or Territory withdraws that consent.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	For the purposes of paragraph\'a0(1)(a), a Minister of a State or Territory may give consent in relation to all State bodies, a class of State bodies, or particular State bodies, of that State or Territory.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 Part\'a02\'97Security standards for smart devices\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 Division\'a01\'97Preliminary\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 12  Simplified outline of this Part\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 The rules may provide mandatory security standards for products that can directly or indirectly connect to the internet (called relevant connectable products) that will be acquired in Australia in specified circumstances.\
If the rules provide a security standard for a product:\
\pard\tqr\tx1786\pardeftab720\li2070\fi-936\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	manufacturers must manufacture the product in compliance with the requirements of the security standard if they are aware, or could reasonably be expected to be aware, that the product will be acquired in Australia in the specified circumstances; and\
	(b)	those manufacturers must also comply with any other obligations relating to the product in the security standard (for example, obligations to publish information about the product); and\
	(c)	if the product does not comply it must not be supplied in Australia if the supplier is aware, or could reasonably be expected to be aware, that the products will be acquired in Australia in those specified circumstances; and\
	(d)	those suppliers must supply the product in Australia accompanied by a statement of compliance.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 A compliance notice, a stop notice and a recall notice may be given for non\uc0\u8209 compliance with obligations in this Part. Internal review may be sought for a decision to issue a notice.\
An independent audit of a product may be undertaken to determine compliance with the requirements of a security standard or requirements for the statement of compliance. The Secretary may request the manufacturer or supplier to provide the product, the statement of compliance or both for the purposes of the audit.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 13  Application of this Part\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	This Part applies to a relevant connectable product that is:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	manufactured on or after the commencement of this Part; or\
	(b)	supplied (other than as second hand goods) on or after the commencement of this Part.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	A 
\f3\i\b relevant connectable product
\f0\i0\b0  is a product that:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	is an internet\uc0\u8209 connectable product or a network\u8209 connectable product; and\
	(b)	is not exempted under the rules.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	For the purposes of paragraph\'a0(2)(b), the rules may specify that:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	classes of products are exempted; or\
	(b)	particular products are exempted.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(4)	An 
\f3\i\b internet\uc0\u8209 connectable product
\f0\i0\b0  is a product that is capable of connecting to the internet using a communication protocol that forms part of the internet protocol suite to send and receive data over the internet.\
	(5)	A 
\f3\i\b network\uc0\u8209 connectable product
\f2\b0  
\f0\i0 is a product that:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	is capable of both sending and receiving data by means of a transmission involving electrical or electromagnetic energy; and\
	(b)	is not an internet\uc0\u8209 connectable product; and\
	(c)	meets the condition in subsection\'a0(6) or (7).\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(6)	A product meets the condition in this subsection if it is capable of connecting directly to an internet\uc0\u8209 connectable product by means of a communication protocol that forms part of the internet protocol suite.\
	(7)	Subject to subsections\'a0(8) and (9), a product meets the condition in this subsection if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	it is capable of connecting directly to 2 or more products at the same time by means of a communication protocol that does not form part of the internet protocol suite; and\
	(b)	it is capable of connecting directly to an internet\uc0\u8209 connectable product by means of such a communication protocol (whether or not at the same time as it connects to any other product).\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(8)	A product consisting of a wire or cable that is used merely to connect the product to another product does not meet the condition in subsection\'a0(7).\
	(9)	If:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	two or more products are designed to be used together for the purposes of facilitating the use of a computer (within the ordinary meaning of that expression); and\
	(b)	at least one of the products (the 
\f3\i\b linking product
\f0\i0\b0 ) is capable of connecting directly to an internet\uc0\u8209 connectable product (whether the computer or some other product) by means of a communication protocol that does not form part of the internet protocol suite; and\
	(c)	each of the products (the 
\f3\i\b input products
\f0\i0\b0 ) that is not a linking product is capable of connecting directly to the linking product, or, if there is more than one linking product, to each linking product:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	wirelessly; and\
	(ii)	by means of a communication protocol that does not form part of the internet protocol suite;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 each of the input products meets the condition in subsection\'a0(7).\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(10)	For the purposes of subsections\'a0(4) to (9), a product is not prevented from being regarded as connecting directly to another product merely because the connection involves the use of a wire or cable.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Division\'a02\'97Security standards for relevant connectable products\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 14  Security standards for relevant connectable products\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	The rules may make provision for, or in relation to, security standards for specified classes of relevant connectable products that will be acquired in Australia in specified circumstances.\
	(2)	Without limiting subsection\'a0(1) a class of relevant connectable products specified for the purposes of that subsection may consist of a particular relevant connectable product or of all relevant connectable products.\
	(3)	Despite subsection\'a014(2) of the 
\f2\i Legislation Act 2003
\f0\i0 , the rules may make provision in relation to a matter by applying, adopting or incorporating, with or without modification, any matter contained in an instrument or other writing as in force or existing from time to time.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 15  Compliance with security standard for a relevant connectable product\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs22 \cf0 Manufacturer must comply\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(1)	An entity must manufacture a relevant connectable product in compliance with the requirements of the security standard for a class of relevant connectable product that will be acquired in Australia in specified circumstances if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the product is included in that class; and\
	(b)	the entity is aware, or could reasonably be expected to be aware, that the product will be acquired in Australia in those circumstances.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	The entity must comply with any other requirements of the security standard that apply to the manufacturer of a product included in that class.\
	(3)	An entity must not supply a product in Australia that was not manufactured in compliance with the requirements of the security standard for a class of relevant connectable product that will be acquired in Australia in specified circumstances if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the product is included in that class; and\
	(b)	the entity is aware, or could reasonably be expected to be aware, that the product will be acquired in Australia in those circumstances.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(4)	The entity must comply with any other requirements of the security standard that apply to the supplier of a product included in that class.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Exception\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(5)	However, to the extent that a requirement in the security standard does not relate to any of the matters in subsection\'a0(6), an entity is not required to comply with subsections\'a0(1) to (4) if the entity is not:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	an entity that is a corporation to which paragraph\'a051(xx) of the Constitution applies; or\
	(b)	an entity that is undertaking activities in the course of, or in relation to, trade or commerce with other countries, among the States, between Territories or between a Territory and a State.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(6)	The matters are the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the direct, or indirect, connection of the relevant connectable product to, a telegraphic, telephonic or other like service within the meaning of paragraph\'a051(v) of the Constitution (including, for example, connection to the internet);\
	(b)	the direct, or indirect, use by the relevant connectable product of such a service (including, for example, use of the internet);\
	(c)	measures that would protect the relevant connectable product from an attack effected by means of such a service (including, for example, by means of the internet).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 16  Obligation to provide and supply products with a statement of compliance with security standard\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs22 \cf0 Manufacturer must provide statement of compliance\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(1)	An entity that manufactures a relevant connectable product must provide, for the supply of the product in Australia, a statement of compliance with the security standard for a class of relevant connectable product that will be acquired in Australia in specified circumstances if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the product is included in that class; and\
	(b)	the entity is aware, or could reasonably be expected to be aware, that the product will be acquired in Australia in those circumstances.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	The entity must retain a copy of the statement of compliance for the period specified in the rules for that class of statements.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Supplier must supply the product with statement of compliance\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(3)	An entity that supplies a relevant connectable product in Australia must supply the product with a statement of compliance with the security standard for a class of relevant connectable product that will be acquired in Australia in specified circumstances if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the product is included in that class; and\
	(b)	the entity is aware, or could reasonably be expected to be aware, that the product will be acquired in Australia in those circumstances.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(4)	The entity must retain a copy of the statement of compliance for the period specified in the rules for that class of statements.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Requirements for statement of compliance\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(5)	The statement of compliance with the security standard under subsection\'a0(1) or (2) must meet the requirements provided by the rules for that class of statements.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Matters relating to the rule making powers\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(6)	Without limiting subsection\'a0(2), (4) or (5) a class of statements may consist of a statement for a particular relevant connectable product or a particular security standard or all relevant connectable products or all security standards.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Division\'a03\'97Enforcement\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 17  Compliance notice\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	The Secretary may give an entity that must comply with an obligation under section\'a015 or 16 a compliance notice if the Secretary:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	is reasonably satisfied that the entity is not complying with the obligation; or\
	(b)	is aware of information that suggests that the entity may not be complying with the obligation.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	The compliance notice must:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	set out the name of the entity to which the notice is given; and\
	(b)	set out brief details of the non\uc0\u8209 compliance or possible non\u8209 compliance; and\
	(c)	specify action within the entity\'92s control that the entity must take in order to address the non\uc0\u8209 compliance or possible non\u8209 compliance; and\
	(d)	specify a reasonable period within which the entity must take the specified action; and\
	(e)	if the Secretary considers it appropriate\'97specify a reasonable period within which the entity must provide the Secretary with evidence that the entity has taken the specified action; and\
	(f)	explain what may happen if the entity does not comply with the notice; and\
	(g)	explain how the entity may seek review of the decision to issue the notice; and\
	(h)	set out any other matters prescribed by the rules.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	Before giving the notice to the entity, the Secretary must:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	notify the entity that the Secretary intends to give the notice to the entity; and\
	(b)	give the entity a specified period (which must not be shorter than 10 days) to make representations about the giving of the notice.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(4)	Only one compliance notice may be given to an entity in relation to a particular instance of the entity\'92s non\uc0\u8209 compliance, or possible non\u8209 compliance, with an obligation under section\'a015 or 16.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 18  Stop notice\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	The Secretary may give an entity that must comply with an obligation under section\'a015 or 16 a stop notice if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the entity has been given a compliance notice under section\'a017 in relation to the non\uc0\u8209 compliance with the obligation; and\
	(b)	the Secretary is reasonably satisfied that:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the entity has not complied with the compliance notice; or\
	(ii)	actions taken by the entity to rectify non\uc0\u8209 compliance with the obligation (whether in accordance with the compliance notice or otherwise) are inadequate to rectify the non\u8209 compliance.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	The stop notice must:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	set out the name of the entity to which the notice is given; and\
	(b)	set out brief details of the non\uc0\u8209 compliance; and\
	(c)	specify action within the entity\'92s control that the entity must take, or refrain from taking, in order to address the non\uc0\u8209 compliance; and\
	(d)	specify a reasonable period within which the entity must take the specified action or refrain from taking the specified action; and\
	(e)	if the Secretary considers it appropriate\'97specify a reasonable period within which the entity must provide the Secretary with evidence that the entity has taken the specified action or refrained from taking the specified action; and\
	(f)	explain what may happen if the entity does not comply with the notice; and\
	(g)	explain how the entity may seek review of the decision to issue the notice; and\
	(h)	set out any other matters prescribed by the rules.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	Before giving the notice to the entity, the Secretary must:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	notify the entity that the Secretary intends to give the notice to the entity; and\
	(b)	give the entity a specified period (which must not be shorter than 10 days) to make representations about the giving of the notice.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(4)	Only one stop notice may be given to an entity in relation to a particular instance of the entity\'92s non\uc0\u8209 compliance with an obligation under section\'a015 or 16.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 19  Recall notice\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	The Secretary may give an entity that must comply with an obligation under section\'a015 or 16 a recall notice if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the entity has been given a stop notice under section\'a018 in relation to the non\uc0\u8209 compliance with the obligation; and\
	(b)	the Secretary is reasonably satisfied that:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the entity has not complied with the stop notice; or\
	(ii)	actions taken by the entity to rectify the non\uc0\u8209 compliance with the obligation (whether in accordance with the compliance notice or otherwise) are inadequate to rectify the non\u8209 compliance.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	The recall notice must:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	set out the name of the entity to which the notice is given; and\
	(b)	set out brief details of the non\uc0\u8209 compliance; and\
	(c)	specify action that the entity must take to do any or all of the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	ensure, to the extent within the entity\'92s control, the product is not acquired in Australia;\
	(ii)	ensure, to the extent within the entity\'92s control, that the product is not supplied to suppliers for supply in Australia;\
	(iii)	arrange for the return, within a specified reasonable period, of the product to the entity, or if the entity is not the manufacturer of the product, the manufacturer of the product; and\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(d)	specify a reasonable period within which the entity must take the specified action; and\
	(e)	if the Secretary considers it appropriate\'97specify a reasonable period within which the entity must provide the Secretary with evidence that the entity has taken the specified action; and\
	(f)	explain what may happen if the entity does not comply with the notice; and\
	(g)	explain how the entity may seek review of the decision to issue the notice; and\
	(h)	set out any other matters prescribed by the rules.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	Before giving the notice to the entity, the Secretary must:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	notify the entity that the Secretary intends to give the notice to the entity; and\
	(b)	give the entity a specified period (which must not be shorter than 10 days) to make representations about the giving of the notice.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(4)	Only one recall notice may be given to an entity in relation to a particular instance of the entity\'92s non\uc0\u8209 compliance with an obligation under section\'a015 or 16.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 20  Public notification of failure to comply with recall notice\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 		If an entity fails to comply with a recall notice, the Minister may publish the following information on the Department\'92s website, or in any other way the Minister considers appropriate:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the identity of the entity;\
	(b)	details of the product;\
	(c)	details of the non\uc0\u8209 compliance;\
	(d)	risks posed by the product relating to the non\uc0\u8209 compliance;\
	(e)	any other matters prescribed by the rules.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Division\'a04\'97Miscellaneous\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 21  Revocation and variation of notices given under this Part\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs22 \cf0 Variation\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(1)	The Secretary may, by notice in writing given to an entity, vary a compliance notice, stop notice or recall notice given under this Part to the entity if the Secretary is reasonably satisfied that the variation is required:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	in order to rectify an error, defect or ambiguity in the notice; or\
	(b)	to adequately rectify the non\uc0\u8209 compliance, or possible non\u8209 compliance, to which the notice relates.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	Before giving the notice to the entity under subsection\'a0(1), the Secretary must:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	notify the entity that the Secretary intends to give the notice to the entity; and\
	(b)	give the entity a specified period (which must not be shorter than 10 days) to make representations about the giving of the notice.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	A varied compliance notice, stop notice or recall notice has the same effect as the original notice for the purposes of this Part.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Revocation\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(4)	The Secretary may, by notice in writing given to an entity, revoke a compliance notice, stop notice or recall notice given under this Part to the entity if the Secretary is no longer satisfied that the grounds for issuing the notice were met.\
	(5)	If a compliance notice, stop notice or recall notice, relating to non\uc0\u8209 compliance or possible non\u8209 compliance by an entity with an obligation, is revoked under subsection\'a0(4), no further notices may be issued under this Part\'a0in relation to that non\u8209 compliance.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 22  Internal review of decision to give compliance, stop or recall notice\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	An entity may apply, in writing, to the Secretary for review (an 
\f3\i\b internal review
\f0\i0\b0 ) of a decision:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	to give the entity a compliance notice under section\'a017; or\
	(b)	to give the entity a stop notice under section\'a018; or\
	(c)	to give the entity a recall notice under section\'a019; or\
	(d)	to vary, under section\'a021, a notice given to the entity.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	An application for an internal review must be made within 30 days after the day on which the notice was given to the entity.\
	(3)	The decision\uc0\u8209 maker for the internal review is:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the Secretary; or\
	(b)	if the Secretary made the decision personally\'97a person:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	to whom the power to issue a notice of that kind has been delegated under section\'a086; and\
	(ii)	that was not involved in the making of the Secretary\'92s decision.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(4)	Within 30 days after the application is received, the decision\uc0\u8209 maker must:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	review the decision; and\
	(b)	affirm, vary or revoke the decision; and\
	(c)	if the decision is revoked\'97make such other decision (if any) that the decision\uc0\u8209 maker thinks appropriate.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(5)	The decision\uc0\u8209 maker for the reviewable decision must, as soon as practicable after making a decision under subsection\'a0(4), give the applicant a written statement of the decision\u8209 maker\'92s reasons for the decision.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 23  Examination to assess compliance with security standard and statement of compliance\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	If an entity must comply with an obligation in section\'a015 or 16 in relation to a relevant connectable product, the Secretary may engage an appropriately qualified and experienced expert to carry out an independent examination of the product to determine either or both of the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	whether the product complies with the security standard for the class of relevant connectable product;\
	(b)	whether the statement of compliance for the product complies with the requirements of section\'a016.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	The expert may examine the product, for example, by doing any of the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	opening any package in which the product is contained;\
	(b)	operating the product;\
	(c)	testing or analysing the product, including through the use of electronic equipment;\
	(d)	if the product contains a record or document\'97reading the record or document either directly or with the use of an electronic device;\
	(e)	taking photographs or video recordings of the product.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Request for product and statement of compliance\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(3)	For the purposes of the examination, the Secretary may request, by notice in writing, the entity to provide the product, or the statement of compliance for the product, or both.\
	(4)	The notice must:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	specify the product; and\
	(b)	if the entity is not the manufacturer\'97specify the manufacturer of the product (if known); and\
	(c)	specify a reasonable period within which the entity must provide the notice; and\
	(d)	specify the period for which the product will be retained for testing; and\
	(e)	specify the requirements of the security standard that the product will be tested against; and\
	(f)	explain the kind of testing or analysis that will be done; and\
	(g)	explain what may happen if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the entity does not comply with the notice; or\
	(ii)	the entity does not comply with its obligations in section\'a015 or 16 in relation to the product; and\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(h)	set out any other matters prescribed by the rules.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Compensation\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(5)	An entity is entitled to be paid by the Commonwealth reasonable compensation for complying with a request under subsection\'a0(3).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 24  Acquisition of property\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 		This Part has no effect to the extent (if any) that its operation would result in an acquisition of property (within the meaning of paragraph\'a051(xxxi) of the Constitution) from a person otherwise than on just terms (within the meaning of that paragraph).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 Part\'a03\'97Ransomware reporting obligations\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 Division\'a01\'97Preliminary\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 25  Simplified outline of this Part\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 This Part\'a0imposes reporting obligations on certain entities who are impacted by a cyber security incident, and who have provided or are aware that another entity has provided, a payment or benefit (called a ransomware payment) to an entity that is seeking to benefit from the impact or the cyber security incident.\
Particular information must be included in a ransomware payment report, including information relating to the cyber security incident, the demand made by the extorting entity and the ransomware payment.\
An entity may be liable to a civil penalty if the entity fails to make a ransomware payment report as required by this Part.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Division\'a02\'97Reporting obligations\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 26  Application of this Part\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	This Part applies if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	an incident has occurred, is occurring or is imminent; and\
	(b)	the incident is a cyber security incident; and\
	(c)	the incident has had, is having, or could reasonably be expected to have, a direct or indirect impact on a reporting business entity; and\
	(d)	an entity (the 
\f3\i\b extorting entity
\f0\i0\b0 ) makes a demand of the reporting business entity, or any other entity, in order to benefit from the incident or the impact on the reporting business entity; and\
	(e)	the reporting business entity provides, or is aware that another entity has provided on their behalf, a payment or benefit (a 
\f3\i\b ransomware payment
\f0\i0\b0 ) to the extorting entity that is directly related to the demand.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	An entity is a 
\f3\i\b reporting business entity
\f0\i0\b0  if, at the time the ransomware payment is made:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the entity:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	is carrying on a business in Australia with an annual turnover for the previous financial year that exceeds the turnover threshold for that year; and\
	(ii)	is not a Commonwealth body or a State body; and\
	(iii)	is not a responsible entity for a critical infrastructure asset; or\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(b)	the entity is a responsible entity for a critical infrastructure asset to which Part\'a02B of the 
\f2\i Security of Critical Infrastructure Act 2018
\f0\i0  applies.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	For the purposes of subparagraph\'a0(2)(a)(i), the 
\f3\i\b turnover threshold
\f1\i0  
\f0\b0 is:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	if a business has been carried on for only part of the previous financial year\'97the amount worked out in the manner prescribed by the rules; or\
	(b)	in any other case\'97the amount prescribed by, or worked out in the manner prescribed by, the rules.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Presumption\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(4)	For the purposes of paragraph\'a0(1)(b), an incident (other than an incident covered by paragraph\'a09(2)(a) or (b)) is presumed to be a cyber security incident if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the incident was probably effected, is probably being effected or could reasonably be expected to be effected, by means of a telegraphic, telephonic or other like service within the meaning of paragraph\'a051(v) of the Constitution (including, for example, by means of the internet); or\
	(b)	the incident has probably impeded or impaired, or is probably impeding or impairing or could reasonably be expected to impede or impair, the ability of a computer to connect to such a service; or\
	(c)	the incident has probably seriously prejudiced, is probably seriously prejudicing, or could reasonably be expected to prejudice:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the social or economic stability of Australia or its people; or\
	(ii)	the defence of Australia; or\
	(iii)	national security.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	Paragraphs 9(2)(a) and (b) cover incidents involving critical infrastructure assets or the activities of corporations to which paragraph\'a051(xx) of the Constitution applies.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(5)	However, subsection\'a0(4) does not make an entity liable to a civil penalty under this Part\'a0if the incident:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	was not in fact effected by means of a telegraphic, telephonic or other like service within the meaning of paragraph\'a051(v) of the Constitution (including, for example, by means of the internet); or\
	(b)	did not in fact impede or impair the ability of a computer to connect to such a service; or\
	(c)	did not in fact seriously prejudice:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the social or economic stability of Australia or its people; or\
	(ii)	the defence of Australia; or\
	(iii)	national security.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 27  Obligation to report following a ransomware payment\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	The reporting business entity must give the designated Commonwealth body a report (a 
\f3\i\b ransomware payment report
\f0\i0\b0 ) that complies with the requirements of this section within 72 hours of making the ransomware payment or becoming aware that the ransomware payment has been made (whichever is applicable).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	For the definition of 
\f3\i\b designated Commonwealth body
\f0\i0\b0 : see section\'a08.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(2)	The ransomware payment report must contain information relating to the following, in accordance with any requirements prescribed by the rules, that, at the time of making the report, the reporting business entity knows or is able, by reasonable search or enquiry, to find out:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	if the reporting business entity made the payment\'97the reporting business entity\'92s contact and business details;\
	(b)	if another entity made the payment\'97that entity\'92s contact and business details;\
	(c)	the cyber security incident, including its impact on the reporting business entity;\
	(d)	the demand made by the extorting entity;\
	(e)	the ransomware payment;\
	(f)	communications with the extorting entity relating to the incident, the demand and the payment.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	The reporting business entity may include other information relating to the cyber security incident in the ransomware payment report.\
	(4)	The ransomware payment report must be given:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	in the form approved by the Secretary (if any); and\
	(b)	in the manner (if any) prescribed by the rules.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(5)	An entity is liable to a civil penalty if the entity contravenes subsection\'a0(1).\
\pard\tx2977\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Civil penalty:	60 penalty units.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(6)	Subsection\'a093(2) of the Regulatory Powers Act does not apply in relation to a contravention of subsection\'a0(1) of this section.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 28  Liability\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	An entity is not liable to an action or other proceeding for damages for or in relation to an act done or omitted in good faith in compliance with section\'a027.\
	(2)	An officer, employee or agent of an entity is not liable to an action for damages for or in relation to an act done or omitted in good faith in connection with an act done or omitted by the entity as mentioned in subsection\'a0(1).\
	(3)	An entity that wishes to rely on subsection\'a0(1) in relation to an action or other proceeding bears an evidential burden (within the meaning of the Regulatory Powers Act) in relation to that matter.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

