\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 Part\'a04\'97Coordination of significant cyber security incidents\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 Division\'a01\'97Preliminary\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 33  Simplified outline of this Part\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 Information may be voluntarily provided to the National Cyber Security Coordinator in relation to significant cyber security incidents.\
The National Cyber Security Coordinator\'92s role is to lead across the whole of Government the coordination and triaging of action in response to a significant cyber security incident.\
Information voluntarily provided under this Part may only be recorded, used and disclosed for limited purposes.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 34  Meaning of 
\f3\i significant cyber security incident
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 		A cyber security incident is a 
\f3\i\b significant cyber security incident
\f2\b0  
\f0\i0 if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	there is a material risk that the incident has seriously prejudiced, is seriously prejudicing, or could reasonably be expected to prejudice:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the social or economic stability of Australia or its people; or\
	(ii)	the defence of Australia; or\
	(iii)	national security; or\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(b)	the incident is, or could reasonably be expected to be, of serious concern to the Australian people.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Division\'a02\'97Voluntary information sharing with the National Cyber Security Coordinator\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 35  Impacted entity may voluntarily provide information to National Cyber Security Coordinator in relation to a significant cyber security incident\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	This section applies if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	an incident has occurred, is occurring or is imminent; and\
	(b)	the incident is a cyber security incident; and\
	(c)	the incident has had, is having, or could reasonably be expected to have, a direct or indirect impact on an entity (the 
\f3\i\b impacted entity
\f0\i0\b0 ); and\
	(d)	the impacted entity is:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	carrying on a business in Australia; or\
	(ii)	a responsible entity for a critical infrastructure asset to which the 
\f2\i Security of Critical Infrastructure Act 2018
\f0\i0  applies.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	The impacted entity, or another entity acting on behalf of the impacted entity, may provide information about the incident to the National Cyber Security Coordinator if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the incident is a significant cyber security incident; or\
	(b)	the incident could reasonably be expected to be a significant cyber security incident.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note 1:	For information provided in relation to other kinds of cyber security incidents: see sections\'a036 and 39.\
Note 2:	This subsection constitutes an authorisation for the National Cyber Security Coordinator to collect the information (including sensitive information) for the purposes of the 
\f2\i Privacy Act 1988
\f0\i0 .\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(3)	Information about the incident may be provided under subsection\'a0(2):\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	at any time during the response to the incident; and\
	(b)	on the impacted entity\'92s own initiative or in response to a request by the National Cyber Security Coordinator.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	There is no obligation on the impacted entity to provide information in response to a request.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs22 \cf0 Presumption\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(4)	For the purposes of paragraph\'a0(1)(b), an incident (other than an incident covered by paragraph\'a09(2)(a) or (b)) is presumed to be a cyber security incident if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the incident was probably effected, is probably being effected or could reasonably be expected to be effected, by means of a telegraphic, telephonic or other like service within the meaning of paragraph\'a051(v) of the Constitution (including, for example, by means of the internet); or\
	(b)	the incident has probably impeded or impaired, or is probably impeding or impairing or could reasonably be expected to impede or impair, the ability of a computer to connect to such a service; or\
	(c)	the incident has probably seriously prejudiced, is probably seriously prejudicing, or could reasonably be expected to prejudice:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the social or economic stability of Australia or its people; or\
	(ii)	the defence of Australia; or\
	(iii)	national security.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	Paragraphs 9(2)(a) and (b) covers incidents involving critical infrastructure assets or the activities of corporations to which paragraph\'a051(xx) of the Constitution applies.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(5)	However, subsection\'a0(4) does not make an entity liable to a civil penalty under this Part\'a0if the incident:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	was not in fact effected by means of a telegraphic, telephonic or other like service within the meaning of paragraph\'a051(v) of the Constitution (including, for example, by means of the internet); or\
	(b)	did not in fact impede or impair the ability of a computer to connect to such a service; or\
	(c)	did not in fact seriously prejudice:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the social or economic stability of Australia or its people; or\
	(ii)	the defence of Australia; or\
	(iii)	national security.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 36  Voluntary provision of information in relation to other incidents or cyber security incidents\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	This section applies if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	an incident has occurred, is occurring or is imminent; and\
	(b)	an entity (the 
\f3\i\b impacted entity
\f0\i0\b0 ) provides information to the National Cyber Security Coordinator in relation to the incident; and\
	(c)	it is unclear at the time the information is provided whether the incident is a cyber security incident or a significant cyber security incident.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	The National Cyber Security Coordinator may collect and use the information for the purposes of determining whether the incident is a cyber security incident or a significant cyber security incident.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	This subsection constitutes an authorisation for the National Cyber Security Coordinator to collect the information (including sensitive information) for the purposes of the 
\f2\i Privacy Act 1988
\f0\i0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 37  Role of the National Cyber Security Coordinator\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 		The role of the National Cyber Security Coordinator includes, but is not limited to, the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	to lead across the whole of Government the coordination and triaging of action in response to a significant cyber security incident;\
	(b)	to inform and advise the Minister and the whole of Government in relation to the whole of Government response to a significant cyber security incident.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Division\'a03\'97Protection of information\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 38  Information provided in relation to a significant cyber security incident\'97use and disclosure by National Cyber Security Coordinator\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs22 \cf0 Permitted use and disclosure\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(1)	The National Cyber Security Coordinator may make a record of, use or disclose information provided under subsection\'a035(2) by, or on behalf of, an entity (the 
\f3\i\b impacted entity
\f0\i0\b0 ) in relation to a cyber security incident but only for the purposes of one or more of the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	assisting the impacted entity, and other entities acting on behalf of the impacted entity, to respond to, mitigate or resolve the cyber security incident;\
	(b)	a permitted cyber security purpose for a cyber security incident.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note 1:	For 
\f3\i\b permitted cyber security purpose 
\f0\i0\b0 for a cyber security incident: see section\'a010. This includes the functions of the National Cyber Security Coordinator under this Part.\
Note 2:	Certain information must not be disclosed to a State body under Parts of this Act unless a Minister of the State or Territory has consented to those Parts applying to the State body: see section\'a011.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs22 \cf0 Restriction on use and disclosure for civil or regulatory action\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(2)	However, the National Cyber Security Coordinator must not make a record of, use or disclose the information for the purposes of investigating or enforcing, or assisting in the investigation or enforcement of, any contravention by the impacted entity of a Commonwealth, State or Territory law other than:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a contravention by the impacted entity of this Part; or\
	(b)	a contravention by the impacted entity of a law that imposes a penalty or sanction for a criminal offence.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	See also section\'a042 in relation to admissibility of the information in proceedings against the impacted entity.\
