\fs24 \cf0 45  Simplified outline of this Part\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 The Cyber Incident Review Board is established by this Part.\
The Board must cause reviews to be conducted in relation to certain cyber security incidents. The purpose of a review is to make recommendations to government and industry about actions that could be taken to prevent, detect, respond to or minimise the impact of, cyber security incidents of a similar nature in the future.\
A review panel will be established for each review in accordance with the terms of reference for the review.\
The Board consists of the Chair and up to 6 other standing members. The standing members are appointed by the Minister.\
The Board may establish an Expert Panel. One or more members of the Expert Panel may be appointed to assist in relation to a review conducted under this Part.\
This Part also deals with the appointment of the Chair, standing members and Expert Panel members, and the procedures of the Board.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Division\'a02\'97Reviews\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 46  Board must cause reviews to be conducted\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	The Cyber Incident Review Board may cause a review to be conducted under this section in relation to a cyber security incident, or a series of related cyber security incidents, on written referral by:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the Minister; or\
	(b)	the National Cyber Security Coordinator; or\
	(c)	an entity impacted by the incident or an incident in the series of incidents; or\
	(d)	a member of the Board.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	Each review is conducted by a particular review panel established for that review in accordance with the terms of reference for the review.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(2)	A review may only be conducted under this section:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	if the Board is satisfied that the incident or series of incidents meets the criteria mentioned in subsection\'a0(3); and\
	(b)	after the incident or series of incidents, and the immediate response, has ended; and\
	(c)	if the Minister has approved the terms of reference for the review.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	For the purposes of paragraph\'a0(2)(a), the criteria are:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the incident or series of incidents have seriously prejudiced, or could reasonably be expected to seriously prejudice:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the social or economic stability of Australia or its people; or\
	(ii)	the defence of Australia; or\
	(iii)	national security; or\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(b)	the incident or series of incidents involved novel or complex methods or technologies, an understanding of which will significantly improve Australia\'92s preparedness, resilience, or response to cyber security incidents of a similar nature; or\
	(c)	the incident or series of incidents are, or could reasonably be expected to be, of serious concern to the Australian people.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(4)	Each review is to be conducted by a review panel that consists of:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the Chair; and\
	(b)	the standing members of the Board that are specified in the terms of reference for the review; and\
	(c)	the members of the Expert Panel appointed to assist in the review under section\'a070.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The terms of reference for the review must specify one or more standing members for the review.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(5)	The rules may make provision for or in relation to reviews under this Part, including for or in relation to the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	dealing with written referrals made to the Board;\
	(b)	prioritisation of referrals for review and reviews conducted;\
	(c)	terms of reference for reviews, including their variation;\
	(d)	notification of reviews;\
	(e)	the timing of when reviews may be conducted;\
	(f)	when reviews may be discontinued;\
	(g)	how information or submissions may be provided for reviews.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 47  Board may discontinue a review\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	The Board may discontinue a review at any time.\
	(2)	The Board must, within 28 days of discontinuing a review, publish in any way the Board considers appropriate notice of the review being discontinued.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 48  Chair may request information or documents\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 		If the Board reasonably believes that:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	an entity; or\
	(b)	a Commonwealth body or a State body; or\
	(c)	an officer or employee of a Commonwealth body or a State body;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 has information or documents relevant to a review being conducted under section\'a046 by a review panel, the Chair may request, by notice in writing,
\f2\i  
\f0\i0 the entity, body, officer or employee to give the Board such information or documents as are specified in the request.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note 1:	There is no requirement to comply with the request.\
Note 2:	The Chair may require certain entities to give documents under section\'a049.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 49  Chair may require certain entities to produce documents\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	This section applies if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the Board reasonably believes that an entity involved in a cyber security incident that relates to a review being conducted under section\'a046 by a review panel has a document that is relevant to the review; and\
	(b)	the Chair of the Board has requested that the entity provide the document under section\'a048; and\
	(c)	the entity is not:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	a Commonwealth body or a State body; or\
	(ii)	an officer or employee of a Commonwealth body or a State body.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	The Chair of the Board may, by notice in writing given to the entity, require the entity to:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	produce any such documents; or\
	(b)	make copies of any such documents and to produce those copies;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 to the Board within the period (which must not be less than 14 days), and in the manner, specified in the notice.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	The notice must set out the effect of the following provisions:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	section\'a050;\
	(b)	Part\'a06 of this Act (Regulatory powers);\
	(c)	sections\'a0137.1 and 137.2 of the 
\f2\i Criminal Code
\f0\i0  (false or misleading information or documents).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Compensation\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(4)	An entity is entitled to be paid by the Commonwealth reasonable compensation for complying with a requirement covered by paragraph\'a0(2)(b).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 50  Civil penalty\'97failing to comply with a notice to produce documents\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	An entity is liable to a civil penalty if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the entity is given a notice under subsection\'a049(2); and\
	(b)	the entity fails to comply with the notice.\
\pard\tx2977\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Civil penalty:	60 penalty units.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	Subsection\'a0(1) does not apply in relation to the production of a document or a copy of a document if the production would, or could reasonably be expected to, prejudice one or more of the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the security, defence or international relations of the Commonwealth;\
	(b)	the capabilities of an intelligence agency;\
	(c)	the prevention, detection or investigation of, or the conduct of proceedings relating to, an offence or a contravention of a civil penalty provision;\
	(d)	the administration of justice.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	Subsection\'a093(2) of the Regulatory Powers Act does not apply in relation to a contravention of subsection\'a0(1) of this section.\
	(4)	Despite section\'a096 of the Regulatory Powers Act, in proceedings for a civil penalty order against an entity for a contravention of subsection\'a0(1), the entity does not bear an evidential burden in relation to the matters in subsection\'a0(2).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	This Act does not make the Crown (other than an authority of the Crown) liable to a civil penalty.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 51  Draft review reports\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	The Board must prepare a draft report (a 
\f3\i\b draft review repor
\f0\i0\b0 t) on a review being conducted under section\'a046 by a review panel.\
	(2)	The draft review report must set out:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the preliminary findings of the review; and\
	(b)	a summary of the information and material on which those preliminary findings are based; and\
	(c)	any recommendations the Board proposes to make; and\
	(d)	if the Board proposes to make recommendations\'97the reasons for those proposed recommendations; and\
	(e)	if the terms of reference for the review require particular information to be included in the draft review report\'97that information; and\
	(f)	information (if any) that is prescribed by the rules; and\
	(g)	such other information that the Board thinks fit to include in the draft review report.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	The Board must give the draft review report to the Minister.\
	(4)	The Board may give the draft review report, or an extract of the draft review report, to any other Commonwealth body or a State body or entity:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	if the Board considers it appropriate to give the body or entity an opportunity to make submissions on the draft review report or the extract; or\
	(b)	for the purposes of determining whether information proposed to be included in the final review report is sensitive review information.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note 1:	The disclosure of sensitive review information may be prohibited under another Act (for example, the 
\f2\i Privacy Act 1988
\f0\i0 ). This section does not authorise disclosure if prohibited under that Act: see subsection\'a0(7) of this section.\
Note 2:	Sensitive review information must be redacted from a final review report that is to be published by the Board: see section\'a053.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(5)	If the Board gives a draft review report to the Minister under subsection\'a0(3), or a Commonwealth body, State body or entity under subsection\'a0(4), the Board must specify a reasonable period within which submissions may be made to the Board on the draft review report.\
	(6)	Submissions must be given in the manner and form (if any) prescribed by the rules.\
	(7)	However, this section does not authorise the Board to record, use or disclose the information to the extent that it is prohibited or restricted by or under the 
\f2\i Privacy Act 1988
\f0\i0  or any other Act.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 52  Final review reports\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	After a review is completed under section\'a046 by the review panel, the Board must prepare a report (a 
\f3\i\b final review report
\f0\i0\b0 ) on the review.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note 1:	The Board must redact sensitive review information from a final review report: see section\'a053.\
Note 2:	If information is redacted from a final review report, the Board must also prepare a protected review report: see section\'a054.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(2)	In preparing the final review report, the Board must consider any submissions received under section\'a051 in relation to the draft review report.\
	(3)	Subject to section\'a053, the final review report must set out:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the findings of the review; and\
	(b)	a summary of the information and material on which those findings are based; and\
	(c)	any recommendations made by the Board; and\
	(d)	if recommendations are made\'97the reasons for those recommendations; and\
	(e)	if the terms of reference for the review require particular information to be included in the review report\'97that information; and\
	(f)	information (if any) that is prescribed by the rules; and\
	(g)	such other information that the Board thinks fit to include in the report.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(4)	The Board must not in the final review report:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	apportion blame in relation to a cyber security incident that was the subject of the review; or\
	(b)	provide the means to determine the liability of any entity in relation to such a cyber security incident; or\
	(c)	identify an individual (unless the individual has consented); or\
	(d)	allow any adverse inference to be drawn from the fact that an entity is the subject of the review.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 However, even though blame or liability may be inferred, or an adverse inference may be made, by a person other than the Board, this does not prevent the Board from including information in the final review report.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(5)	This section does not otherwise limit what may be included in the final review report.\
	(6)	The Board must publish the final review report (excluding any information required to be redacted under section\'a053). The report may be published in any way the Board considers appropriate.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 53  Certain information must be redacted from final review reports\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	Information must be redacted from a final review report if the Chair is satisfied that the information is sensitive review information.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	If information is redacted from a final review report, the Board must prepare a protected review report that includes the information, see section\'a054.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(2)	
\f3\i\b Sensitive review information
\f0\i0\b0  is information the disclosure of which:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	could prejudice the security, defence or international relations of Australia; or\
	(b)	would prejudice relations between the Commonwealth government and the government of a State or Territory; or\
	(c)	could reveal, or enable a person to ascertain, the existence or identity of a confidential source of information in relation to the enforcement of the criminal law; or\
	(d)	could endanger a person\'92s life or physical safety; or\
	(e)	would prejudice the fair trial of any person or the impartial adjudication of a matter; or\
	(f)	would involve disclosing information whose disclosure is prohibited or restricted by or under this Act, another Act or an instrument made under an Act; or\
	(g)	would involve unreasonably disclosing information that is confidential or commercially sensitive; or\
	(h)	would involve the disclosure of personal information about an individual without their consent.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 54  Protected review reports\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	If information must be redacted from a final review report under section\'a053, the Board must prepare another report (a
\f3\i\b  protected review report
\f0\i0\b0 ) that includes:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the redacted information; and\
	(b)	the reasons for redacting the information from the final review report.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	If a protected review report is prepared under this section, the Board must give the Minister, and the Prime Minister, a copy of:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the final review report prepared under section\'a052; and\
	(b)	a copy of the protected review report.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	The Minister may give a copy of the protected review report, or an extract of the protected review report, to any other Commonwealth body, a State body or an entity but only for the purposes of one or more of the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the performance of the functions of a Commonwealth body relating to responding to, mitigating or resolving a cyber security incident;\
	(b)	the performance of the functions of a State body relating to responding to, mitigating or resolving a cyber security incident;\
	(c)	informing and advising the Minister, and other Ministers of the Commonwealth, about a cyber security incident;\
	(d)	the performance of the functions of an intelligence agency.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Division\'a03\'97Protection of information relating to reviews\
\pard\tqc\tx4150\tqr\tx8307\pardeftab720\ri1933\sl-160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs16 \cf0   \
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 55  Limitations on use and disclosure by the Board\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs22 \cf0 Permitted use and disclosure\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(1)	The Board may make a record of, use or disclose information provided by an entity, Commonwealth body or State body under section\'a048, 49 or 51 but only:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	for the purposes of one or more of the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	performing functions or exercising powers under this Part or Part\'a06 as it applies to this Part;\
	(ii)	proceedings under, or arising out of, section\'a0137.1 or 137.2 of the 
\f2\i Criminal Code 
\f0\i0 (false and misleading information and documents) that relate to this Act;\
	(iii)	proceedings for an offence against section\'a0149.1 of the 
\f2\i Criminal Code
\f0\i0  (which deals with obstruction of Commonwealth public officials) that relates to this Act;\
	(iv)	the performance of the functions of a Commonwealth body relating to responding to, mitigating or resolving a cyber security incident;\
	(v)	the performance of the functions of a State body relating to responding to, mitigating or resolving a cyber security incident;\
	(vi)	informing and advising the Minister, and other Ministers of the Commonwealth, about a cyber security incident;\
	(vii)	the performance of the functions of an intelligence agency; or\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(b)	as otherwise authorised by a provision of this Part.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	Certain information must not be disclosed to a State body under Parts of this Act unless a Minister of the State or Territory has consented to those Parts applying to the State body: see section\'a011.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs22 \cf0 Restriction on use and disclosure for civil or regulatory action\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(2)	However, the Board must not make a record of, use or disclose the information for the purposes of investigating or enforcing, or assisting in the investigation or enforcement of, any contravention by the entity or body of a Commonwealth, State or Territory law other than:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a contravention by the entity or body of this Part; or\
	(b)	a contravention by the entity or body of a law that imposes a penalty or sanction for a criminal offence.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	See also section\'a058 in relation to admissibility of the information in proceedings.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs22 \cf0 Interaction with the Privacy Act 1988\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	
\f0\i0 (3)	Subsection\'a0(1) does not authorise the Board to record, use or disclose the information to the extent that it is prohibited or restricted by or under
\f2\i  
\f0\i0 the 
\f2\i Privacy Act 1988
\f0\i0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Information not covered by the prohibitions in this section\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(4)	Subsection\'a0(1) does not prohibit the recording, use or disclosure of information that has already been lawfully made available to the public
\f4\fs20 .
\f0\fs22 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 56  Limitations on secondary use and disclosure\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	This section applies to information that:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	has been provided to the Board under section\'a048, 49 or 51; and\
	(b)	has been obtained under section\'a054 or 55, or this section, by an entity, a Commonwealth body or a State body; and\
	(c)	is held by the entity, Commonwealth body or State body.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	This section does not apply to the information to the extent that it has been otherwise obtained by the entity, Commonwealth body or State body.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs22 \cf0 Permitted use and disclosure\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(2)	The entity, Commonwealth body or State body may make a record of, use or disclose the information but only:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	for the purposes of one or more of the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	performing functions or exercising powers, or assisting in the performance of functions or the exercise of powers, under this Part or Part\'a06 as it applies to this Part;\
	(ii)	proceedings under, or arising out of, section\'a0137.1 or 137.2 of the 
\f2\i Criminal Code
\f0\i0  (false and misleading information and documents) that relate to this Act;\
	(iii)	proceedings for an offence against section\'a0149.1 of the 
\f2\i Criminal Code
\f0\i0  (which deals with obstruction of Commonwealth public officials) that relates to this Act;\
	(iv)	the performance of the functions of a Commonwealth body relating to responding to, mitigating or resolving a cyber security incident;\
	(v)	the performance of the functions of a State body relating to responding to, mitigating or resolving a cyber security incident;\
	(vi)	informing and advising the Minister, and other Ministers of the Commonwealth, about a cyber security incident;\
	(vii)	the performance of the functions of an intelligence agency; or\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(b)	as otherwise authorised by a provision of this Part.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Restriction on use and disclosure for civil or regulatory action\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(3)	However, the entity, Commonwealth body or State body must not make a record of, use or disclose the information for the purposes of investigating or enforcing, or assisting in the investigation or enforcement of, any contravention, by the entity or body that originally provided the information under section\'a048, 49 or 51, of a Commonwealth, State or Territory law other than:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a contravention by the entity or body of this Part; or\
	(b)	a contravention by the entity or body of a law that imposes a penalty or sanction for a criminal offence.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	See also section\'a058 in relation to admissibility of the information in proceedings.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs22 \cf0 Interaction with the Privacy Act 1988\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	
\f0\i0 (4)	Subsection\'a0(2) does not authorise the entity, Commonwealth body or State body to record, use or disclose the information to the extent that it is prohibited or restricted by or under
\f2\i  
\f0\i0 the 
\f2\i Privacy Act 1988
\f0\i0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Information not covered by the prohibitions in this section\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(5)	Subsection\'a0(2) does not prohibit:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	recording, use or disclosure of information that has already been lawfully made available to the public (for example, in the publication of the final review report); or\
	(b)	if the entity is an individual\'97recording, use or disclosure of personal information about the individual; or\
	(c)	if the entity or body is the entity or body that originally provided the information under section\'a048, 49 or 51\'97the entity\'92s or body\'92s own information; or\
	(d)	recording, use or disclosure of that entity\'92s or body\'92s own information, with the consent of that entity or body, by another entity, a Commonwealth body or a State body; or\
	(e)	recording, use or disclosure of information for the purposes of carrying out a State\'92s constitutional functions, powers or duties.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Civil penalty for contravention of this section\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf0 	(6)	An entity is liable to a civil penalty if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the entity contravenes subsection\'a0(2); and\
	(b)	the entity is not a Commonwealth officer; and\
	(c)	any of the following applies:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the information is sensitive information about an individual and the individual has not consented to the record, use or disclosure of the information;\
	(ii)	the information is confidential or commercially sensitive;\
	(iii)	the record, use or disclosure of the information would, or could reasonably be expected to, cause damage to the security, defence or international relations of the Commonwealth.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note 1:	See the 
\f2\i Criminal Code 
\f0\i0 for offences for Commonwealth officers.\
Note 2:	This Act does not make the Crown (other than an authority of the Crown) liable to a civil penalty.\
\pard\tx2977\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 Civil penalty:	60 penalty units.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 57  Legal professional privilege\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	The fact that an entity provided information to the Board under section\'a048, 49 or 51 does not otherwise affect a claim of legal professional privilege that anyone may make in relation to that information in any proceedings:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	under any Commonwealth, State or Territory law (including the common law); or\
	(b)	before a tribunal of the Commonwealth, a State or a Territory.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	Despite subsection\'a0(1), this section does not apply to the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the proceedings of a coronial inquiry or a Royal Commission in Australia;\
	(b)	proceedings in a federal court exercising original jurisdiction in which a writ of mandamus or prohibition or an injunction is sought against an officer or officers of the Commonwealth.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li2353\fi-709\ri1933\sl-198\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	For 
\f3\i\b federal court
\f0\i0\b0 , see section\'a02B of the 
\f2\i Acts Interpretation Act 1901
\f0\i0 .\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(3)	This section does not limit or affect any right, privilege or immunity that the entity has, apart from this section, as a defendant in any proceedings.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 58  Admissibility of information given by an entity that has been requested or required by the Board\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	This section applies to information that:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	has been provided by an entity to the Board under section\'a048, 49 or 51; and\
	(b)	has been obtained under section\'a048, 49, 51, 54, 55 or 56 by a Commonwealth body or a State body; and\
	(c)	is held by the Commonwealth body or State body.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	This section does not apply to information held by the Commonwealth body or State body to the extent that it has been otherwise obtained.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(2)	The information is not admissible in evidence against the entity in any of the following proceedings:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	criminal proceedings for an offence under a Commonwealth law, other than:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	proceedings for an offence against section\'a0137.1 or 137.2 of the 
\f2\i Criminal Code
\f0\i0  (which deal with false or misleading information or documents) that relates to this Act; or\
	(ii)	proceedings for an offence against section\'a0149.1 of the 
\f2\i Criminal Code 
\f0\i0 (which deals with obstruction of Commonwealth public officials) that relates to this Act;\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(b)	civil proceedings for a contravention of a civil penalty provision of a Commonwealth law, other than a civil penalty provision of this Part;\
	(c)	proceedings for a breach of any other Commonwealth, State or Territory law (including the common law);\
	(d)	proceedings before a tribunal of the Commonwealth, a State or a Territory.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(4)	This section does not apply to the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the proceedings of a coronial inquiry or a Royal Commission in Australia;\
	(b)	proceedings in a federal court exercising original jurisdiction in which a writ of mandamus or prohibition or an injunction is sought against an officer or officers of the Commonwealth.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li2353\fi-709\ri1933\sl-198\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	For 
\f3\i\b federal court
\f0\i0\b0 , see section\'a02B of the 
\f2\i Acts Interpretation Act 1901
\f0\i0 .\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(5)	This section does not limit or affect any right, privilege or immunity that the entity has, apart from this section, as a defendant in any proceedings.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 59  Disclosure of draft review reports prohibited\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	An entity is liable to a civil penalty if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the entity receives a draft review report under section\'a051; and\
	(b)	the entity makes a record of, discloses or otherwise uses any information in the draft review report.\
\pard\tx2977\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Civil penalty:	60 penalty units.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	Subsection\'a0(1) does not apply if the making of the record, disclosure or use is:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	for the purpose of preparing a submission to the Board in accordance with section\'a051; or\
	(b)	if the entity is the entity that originally provided the information under section\'a048 or 49\'97of the entity\'92s own information; or\
	(c)	with the consent of the Chair of the Board; or\
	(d)	after the information has already been lawfully made available to the public (for example, in the publication of the final review report);\
	(e)	for the purposes of carrying out a State\'92s constitutional functions, powers or duties.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	Despite section\'a096 of the Regulatory Powers Act, in proceedings for a civil penalty order against an entity for a contravention of subsection\'a0(1), the entity does not bear an evidential burden in relation to the matters in subsection\'a0(2).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	This Act does not make the Crown (other than an authority of the Crown) liable to a civil penalty.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Division\'a04\'97Establishment, functions and powers of the Board\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 60  Cyber Incident Review Board\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	The Cyber Incident Review Board is established by this section.\
	(2)	For the purposes of paragraph\'a0(a) of the definition of 
\f3\i\b Department of State
\f0\i0\b0  in section\'a08 of the 
\f2\i Public Governance, Performance and Accountability Act 2013
\f0\i0 , the Cyber Incident Review Board is prescribed in relation to the Department.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	Subject to subsection\'a0(2), this means that the chair and members of the Board are officials of the Department for the purposes of the 
\f2\i Public Governance, Performance and Accountability Act 2013
\f0\i0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 61  Constitution of the Board\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 		The Board consists of the following members:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a Chair;\
	(b)	at least 2, and not more than 6, other standing members.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 62  Functions of the Board\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	The functions of the Board are:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	to cause reviews to be conducted by review panels in relation to cyber security incidents, or series of related cyber security incidents, to:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	identify factors that contributed to the incident or series of incidents; and\
	(ii)	make recommendations to government and industry about actions that could be taken to prevent, detect, respond to or minimise the impact of, incidents of a similar nature in the future; and\
	(iii)	report publicly on the review; and\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(b)	any other functions conferred on the Board by this Act or the rules.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	See section\'a046 in relation to the circumstances in which a cyber security incident may be reviewed.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(2)	It is not a function of the Board to:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	apportion blame in relation to a cyber security incident; or\
	(b)	provide the means to determine the liability of any entity in relation to a cyber security incident; or\
	(c)	allow any adverse inference to be drawn from the fact that an entity is the subject of a review.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 However, even though blame or liability may be inferred, or an adverse inference may be made, by a person other than the Board, this does not prevent the Board from carrying out its functions.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	The Board has power to do all things necessary or convenient to be done for or in connection with the performance of the Board\'92s functions.\
	(4)	The Board must not perform a function or exercise a power under this Part at a particular time if the performance of the function or the exercise of the power at that time would prejudice the investigation of, or the conduct of proceedings relating to, an offence or a contravention of a civil penalty provision under a law of the Commonwealth or of a State or Territory.\
	(5)	The rules may prescribe the circumstances in which cyber security incidents are a series of related incidents for the purposes of this section.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	For example, the rules may prescribe that cyber security incidents are a series of related incidents if the incidents involve a common type of impacted system or a common attack method.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 63  Independence\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Subject to this Act and to other laws of the Commonwealth, the Cyber Incident Review Board:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	has complete discretion in the performance of the Board\'92s functions and the exercise of the Board\'92s powers; and\
	(b)	is not subject to direction by any person in relation to the performance or exercise of those functions or powers.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	The Minister must approve the terms of reference for a review to be undertaken by the Board: see subsection\'a046(2).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Division\'a05\'97Terms and conditions of appointment of the Chair and members of the Board\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 64  Appointment of Chair\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	The Chair of the Board is to be appointed by the Minister by written instrument.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	The Chair may be reappointed: see section\'a033AA of the 
\f2\i Acts Interpretation Act 1901
\f0\i0 .\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(2)	The Chair may be appointed on a full\uc0\u8209 time or part\u8209 time basis.\
	(3)	The Chair holds office for the period specified in the instrument of appointment. The period must not exceed 4 years.\
	(4)	The rules may make provision for or in relation to the appointment of the Chair, including in relation to eligibility for appointment.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 65  Remuneration of the Chair\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	The Chair of the Board is to be paid the remuneration that is determined by the Remuneration Tribunal. If no determination of that remuneration by the Tribunal is in operation, the Chair is to be paid the remuneration that is prescribed by the rules.\
	(2)	The Chair is to be paid the allowances that are prescribed by the rules.\
	(3)	This section has effect subject to the 
\f2\i Remuneration Tribunal Act 1973
\f0\i0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 66  Appointment of standing members of the Board\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	A standing member of the Board is to be appointed by the Minister by written instrument.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	A member may be reappointed: see section\'a033AA of the 
\f2\i Acts Interpretation Act 1901
\f0\i0 .\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(2)	A standing member of the Board may be appointed on a full\uc0\u8209 time or part\u8209 time basis.\
	(3)	A standing member of the Board holds office for the period specified in the instrument of appointment. The period must not exceed 4 years.\
	(4)	The rules may make provision for or in relation to the appointment of standing members of the Board, including in relation to eligibility for appointment.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 67  Remuneration of standing members of the Board\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	A standing member of the Board is to be paid the remuneration that is determined by the Remuneration Tribunal. If no determination of that remuneration by the Tribunal is in operation, a standing member of the Board is to be paid the remuneration that is prescribed by the rules.\
	(2)	A standing member of the Board is to be paid the allowances that are prescribed by the rules.\
	(3)	This section has effect subject to the 
\f2\i Remuneration Tribunal Act 1973
\f0\i0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 68  Acting Chair\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 		The Minister may, by written instrument, appoint a standing member of the Board to act as the Chair:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	during a vacancy in the office of Chair (whether or not an appointment has previously been made to the office); or\
	(b)	during any period, or during all periods, when the Chair:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	is absent from duty or from Australia; or\
	(ii)	is, for any reason, unable to perform the duties of the office.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	For rules that apply to acting appointments, see section\'a033A of the 
\f2\i Acts Interpretation Act 1901
\f0\i0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 69  Terms and conditions etc. for standing members\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	The rules may make provision for or in relation to the Board, including for or in relation to the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	membership of the Board (subject to section\'a061);\
	(b)	terms of appointment of the Chair and standing members;\
	(c)	acting appointments;\
	(d)	resignation of the Chair and standing members;\
	(e)	disclosure of interests by the Chair and standing members;\
	(f)	termination of appointment of the Chair and standing members;\
	(g)	leave of absence of the Chair and standing members.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	The Chair and a standing member of the Board holds office on the terms and conditions (if any) that are determined by the Minister in relation to matters not covered by this Act or the rules.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

