\fs24 \cf0 78  Simplified outline of this Part\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs22 \cf0 Each civil penalty provision of this Act, and of Division\'a01A of Part\'a06 of the 
\f2\i Intelligence Services Act 2001
\f0\i0 , is subject to:\
\pard\tqr\tx1786\pardeftab720\li2070\fi-936\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	monitoring under Part\'a02 of the Regulatory Powers Act; and\
	(b)	investigation under Part\'a03 of the Regulatory Powers Act.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Sections\'a015 and 16 of this Act (regarding security standards) are also subject to monitoring under Part\'a02 of the Regulatory Powers Act.\
Civil penalty orders may be sought under Part\'a04 of the Regulatory Powers Act from a relevant court in relation to contraventions of such civil penalty provisions.\
Infringement notices may be given under Part\'a05 of the Regulatory Powers Act for alleged contraventions of such civil penalty provisions.\
Undertakings to comply with such civil penalty provisions, and sections\'a015 and 16 (regarding security standards), may be accepted and enforced under Part\'a06 of the Regulatory Powers Act.\
Injunctions under Part\'a07 of the Regulatory Powers Act may be used to restrain a person from contravening, or to compel compliance with, such civil penalty provisions.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

